font color=#FFFF33>(2/4/03 12:27:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A Hellish Night in Droga</span><hr size=1> …and we followed Him, believing His words on how easy it was going to be.  Deknyr and I knew that Droga was a place of hell and that nothing good would come out of it.  But still we followed…<br>
<br>
Was it friendship for him that drove us into this hellish night?  Was it because we did not want him alone among the goblins?  He sounded so sure of Himself and we thought, with Him by our side, what could possibly go wrong.  <br>
<br>
His map was inaccurate; we got lost many times, evaded so many angry goblins and then the nightmare started.  We fell in a disguised hole on the ground and landed in a locked jail with more goblins lurking around.  <br>
<br>
Evac He said, Evac!  Sure, we were all camouflaged then but by casting the spell I was visible again and the enraged goblins battered me, pounded on me with gnashing teeth and I prayed to Tunare that we would be safe.  There was a ray of hope; we did escape but only to fall pray on another angry goblin.  Being already so weak, I died.<br>
<br>
I awoke partially naked in a land surprisingly beautiful and peaceful.  Birds singing everywhere.  Fields of green with flowers and trees.  <br>
<br>
“Where am I?  What am I doing here?”  I take a few steps and notice I am alone.  I call their names…Watchyur?  Deknyr?  No one answers.  Did I die? Is this where you go when you die?<br>
<br>
I hear the noise of a babbling brook nearby and I walk in its direction.  While bending down on its banks to quench my thirst, I hear a voice from far away saying to me…”I am sorry love” My eyes fill with tears.  Suddenly, I hear Ajlea whispering to me that all will be fine child.  Another flash of light and I am back in hell. I can feel my bruises, my pain.  I see Deknyr near by and also beloved Ajlea who brought me back to life.  And I sit to recover from the ordeal.<br>
<br>
I was told that after my death, He went back and He also died.  I called upon Lord Peraspera to assist us in this dangerous mission of retrieving the dead and he came as fast as he could.  Even our beloved Sonjaleah came to our aid.  <br>
<br>
The three of us died that frightful night. As for me, I died twice. I am very distressed that we got Lady Sonjaleah and Lord Peraspera involved in this incredible rescue. I thank the Blessed Tunare for giving me such good friends I can rely on because frankly, for the first time in my young life I saw no hope…No hope. <br>
 <br>
Sitting in my warm bed in Kelethin, nursing my wounds, I scribe the final words of this horrible event in my diary…Three times He told me He was sorry…<br>
<br>
Unable to control the overwhelming urge to cry, I turn my face to my pillow and let it all out.<br>
